{"version": 2, "width": 133, "height": 33, "timestamp": 1782860052, "env": {"SHELL": "/bin/bash", "TERM": "xterm-256color"}}
[0.045273, "o", "------------------------------------------------------------------\r\n"]
[0.052196, "o", "  FENGARDE — an open-source SIEM pipeline.\r\n\r\n  Raw security logs in  ->  one schema (OCSF)  ->  correlation rules  ->  real alerts.\r\n  Every service is decoupled and talks only over a message bus.\r\n\r\n  This demo runs the v0.1 acceptance test with ZERO infrastructure:\r\n  no Docker, no Redis, no OpenSearch — just the in-memory bus.\r\n"]
[0.054268, "o", "------------------------------------------------------------------\r\n\r\n# The signal: 10 failed SSH logins from a single IP (203.0.113.5) within 60s.\r\n"]
[0.054725, "o", "\r\n# The whole pipeline runs in-process: normalize -> detect -> triage -> index.\r\n\r\n# Watch for the brute-force ALERT, then a replay that DEDUPES (idempotent).\r\n"]
[0.055187, "o", "\r\n$ python tools/demo_e2e.py\r\n"]
[4.503046, "o", "WS-2 normalized=10 dropped=0\r\nWS-4 scored=10 alerts=1 ai=1\r\nWS-5 analyzed=1 (passthrough stub)\r\nWS-3 indexed=12 dup=0 unroutable=1\r\n\r\n  ALERT: Authentication brute-force from single source src=203.0.113.5 score=70 id=6f1c8a2e-0d3b-4c11-9a21-7b5e2f9a1c01:203.0.113.5:29166666\r\n"]
[4.762235, "o", "  T7 OK: replay reused alert_id 6f1c8a2e-0d3b-4c11-9a21-7b5e2f9a1c01:203.0.113.5:29166666 -> deduped (alerts count stayed 2)\r\n\r\n[OK] FENGARDE v0.1 acceptance: SSH brute-force -> real alert in the index, idempotent under replay. Zero infra.\r\n"]
[4.795741, "o", "------------------------------------------------------------------\r\n"]
[4.802258, "o", "  That alert is real, not mock data: the brute-force rule fired on the 10th\r\n  failure, the alert reached the index, and replaying the event reused the same\r\n  alert id instead of duplicating it.\r\n\r\n  Try the live Dockerized stack:   make up   ->   http://localhost:8080\r\n  Add a parser without Docker:      cd services/ws2-normalization && python test_contract.py\r\n"]
[4.805747, "o", "------------------------------------------------------------------\r\n"]
